.TH "LIGHTNING-WALLET-SEED-VERIFY" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-wallet-seed-verify \- check that a seed is stored in the wallet database
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning wallet-seed-verify
.RI [ wallet ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Queries the wallet SQLite database for the presence of a
.B seed
entry in the
.B secrets
table.
Defaults to the
.B default
wallet.
Returns
.B {"ok":false}
if the database does not exist.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"ok":true,"seed_present":true|false}
{"ok":false,"reason":...}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-wallet-check (1),
.BR lightning-wallet-migrate (1)
